802
00:56:49,928 --> 00:56:54,889
Ld Templeton: I let Europe nd the aftermath of the war wash over me.

803
00:56:54,976 --> 00:57:01,200
But Billy, Billy's faith was
unshaken by what he saw.

804
00:57:01,287 --> 00:57:06,510
How could that be?

805
00:57:06,597 --> 00:57:08,512
And then we came back.

806
00:57:08,599 --> 00:57:10,862
Billy: Ruth, I'm home!

807
00:57:10,949 --> 00:57:12,211
I brought Chuck back
for dinner!

808
00:57:12,298 --> 00:57:14,213
Ruth: I'm in your office.

809
00:57:14,300 --> 00:57:17,477
Billy: Hi.

810
00:57:19,044 --> 00:57:21,046
Ruth: I missed you.

811
00:57:21,133 --> 00:57:22,351
Hello, Chuck.

812
00:57:22,439 --> 00:57:23,831
Young Templeton:
Hello, Ruth.

813
00:57:23,918 --> 00:57:25,442
Billy: So, what were you
doin' up there?

814
00:57:25,529 --> 00:57:26,965
Ruth: Oh, just measurin'
for new curtains.

815
00:57:27,052 --> 00:57:28,270
Billy: Oh honey, I don't need
any new curtains.

816
00:57:28,357 --> 00:57:29,881
Ruth: Well, they're not
for you.

817
00:57:29,968 --> 00:57:30,882
Billy: Who are they for?
This is my office.

818
00:57:30,969 --> 00:57:32,579
Ruth: Well, not for long.

819
00:57:32,666 --> 00:57:33,928
Billy: Honey, I have to have
a place to do my work.

820
00:57:34,015 --> 00:57:36,061
Ruth: They're for
the nursery.

821
00:57:36,148 --> 00:57:38,237
Billy: Well, I need a place
to write, and do my sermons,
and...

822
00:57:38,324 --> 00:57:40,152
Billy: Nursery?Ruth: Mm-hm.

823
00:57:40,239 --> 00:57:41,588
Billy: Nursery, like for plants?

824
00:57:41,675 --> 00:57:45,244
Ruth: For babies.Billy: For baby plants?

