at least 10,000.

867
01:01:07,315 --> 01:01:08,360
Billy: We need 25,000.

868
01:01:08,447 --> 01:01:11,450
T.w.: 25,000?

869
01:01:11,537 --> 01:01:14,192
Billy: What about Charles?
Is he on board?

870
01:01:14,279 --> 01:01:17,369
T.w.: No.

871
01:01:17,456 --> 01:01:22,374
Billy: Then to do it right,
we need $25,000.

872
01:01:22,461 --> 01:01:24,463
Reporter: Tell US
about the scandal,

873
01:01:24,550 --> 01:01:28,423
Billy Graham and the picture
holding the sack of money.

874
01:01:28,510 --> 01:01:33,124
Old Templeton: Oh, that.

875
01:01:33,211 --> 01:01:40,131
In those days, the, ah,
the final offering in churches,
and tents, and halls-

876
01:01:40,218 --> 01:01:42,394
I mean, they used to call it
the "love offering."

877
01:01:42,481 --> 01:01:44,396
It would go to cover
the evangelists' expenses

878
01:01:44,483 --> 01:01:47,138
and, and go on
to the next campaign.

879
01:01:47,225 --> 01:01:58,192
And anyway, some ambitious
reporter takes a picture
of Billy with the money.

880
01:01:58,279 --> 01:01:59,759
It was nonsense.

881
01:01:59,846 --> 01:02:03,154
I mean, Billy made sure
that he was accountable

882
01:02:03,241 --> 01:02:05,330
for every penny collected.

883
01:02:05,417 --> 01:02:07,549
He was completely transparent.

884
01:02:07,636 --> 01:02:12,424
One day, he said, "now boys, I,
I want you to go to your rooms,

885
01:02:12,511 --> 01:02:14,469
and I want you write down
the things

886
01:02:14,556 --> 01:02:18,169
that can cause the downfall
of an evangelist."

887
01:02:18,256 --> 01:02:20,562
They all had the same items.

888
01:02:20,649 --> 01:02:24,828
And Billy said, "alright fellas,
these are the rules:

889
01:02:24,915 --> 01:02:29,310
From now on, no man
is to be in a room

890
01:02:29,397 --> 01:02:33,837
alone with a woman
other than his wife."

891
01:02:33,924 --> 01:02:36,491
He said, "we're not even
going to let there be

892
01:02:36,578 --> 01:02:41,366
a breath of scandal
in this ministry."

893
01:02:41,453 --> 01:02:48,547
I mean, Billy Graham is the most
scrupulously honest person

894
01:02:48,634 --> 01:02:52,856
that I have ever met.

895
01:02:52,943 --> 01:02:59,776
And when I needed a friend,
he was always there.

896
01:03:02,474 --> 01:03:07,392
Young Templeton:
Bill, how can anyone

897
01:03:07,479 --> 01:03:12,876
take the Bible as literal
word of god?

898
01:03:12,963 --> 01:03:14,181
Billy: What do you mean?

899
01:03:14,268 --> 01:03:16,531
Young Templeton: Jonah
and the whale.

900
01:03:16,618 --> 01:03:19,883
Do you think that a whale
actually swallowed a man
and spat him out?

901
01:03:19,970 --> 01:03:22,886
Or, or, or that god made
the sun stand still in the sky.

902
01:03:22,973 --> 01:03:27,412
Do you honestly believe that
the earth stopped revolving?

903
01:03:27,499 --> 01:03:31,895
Where is the hard science
to back these stories up?

904
01:03:31,982 --> 01:03:36,464
And if the Bible is not true
in each and every case,

905
01:03:36,551 --> 01:03:40,904
then doesn't that cast doubt
on all of it?

906
01:03:40,991 --> 01:03:43,428
Billy: Charles, it's the word
of god.

907
01:03:43,515 --> 01:03:46,257
Young Templeton: But what if
it's wrong, Billy?

908
01:03:46,344 --> 01:03:51,262
Nothing more than feeble stories
written by men like you and me,

909
01:03:51,349 --> 01:03:55,919
attempting to answer
the great questions of life.

910
01:03:56,006 --> 01:04:02,621
If it's wrong, then what
about the rest?

911
01:04:10,368 --> 01:04:17,941
Old Templeton: He went down
his path...

912
01:04:18,028 --> 01:04:20,334
I went down another.

913
01:04:29,778 --> 01:04:31,432
Young Templeton:
Good evening, everyone.

914
01:04:31,519 --> 01:04:35,959
Thank you so much
for coming out tonight.

915
01:04:36,046 --> 01:04:42,313
As I look out, I see a lot
of familiar faces.

916
01:04:42,400 --> 01:04:47,492
I've known some of you since
you came into this world.

917
01:04:47,579 --> 01:04:51,975
I have seen some of you
through times, good,

918
01:04:52,062 --> 01:04:54,673
and through times not so good.

919
01:04:54,760 --> 01:05:04,378
And it has been my honor,
my deepest honor,
to serve you.

920
01:05:04,465 --> 01:05:13,997
But I am here
with heavy heart.

921
01:05:14,084 --> 01:05:19,002
In me, you put your trust
for spiritual guidance,

922
01:05:19,089 --> 01:05:22,353
and I realize the responsibility
and the honor of this.

923
01:05:22,440 --> 01:05:29,708
I realize it to the center
of my core.

924
01:05:29,795 --> 01:05:40,371
And so, it pains me,
but I must confess this.

925
01:05:40,458 --> 01:05:45,463
I find that I can no longer
accept many of the tenets,

926
01:05:45,550 --> 01:05:57,040
the fundamental tenets,
of the Christian faith.

927
01:05:57,127 --> 01:05:59,216
I see now that there are
other truths-

928
01:05:59,303 --> 01:06:04,047
that there are other paths,
other perspectives,
other ways.

929
01:06:04,134 --> 01:06:10,749
So, to continue on this journey
toward greater understanding,

930
01:06:10,836 --> 01:06:21,673
toward an ever-widening
search for truth,

931
01:06:21,760 --> 01:06:25,459
I've accepted a position
at Princeton university.

932
01:06:25,546 --> 01:06:35,513
[Instrumental music]

933
01:06:35,600 --> 01:06:44,739
[Instrumental music]

934
01:06:44,826 --> 01:06:55,446
Young Templeton: And this means
that I am leaving this ministry.

935
01:06:55,533 --> 01:07:01,104
Billy: Charles Templeton
is my best friend,

936
01:07:01,191 --> 01:07:08,546
and there is nothing
dishonest in that man.

937
01:07:08,633 --> 01:07:11,636
And, because of a crisis
of his faith,

938
01:07:11,723 --> 01:07:17,642
he felt a moral imperative
to resign from his positions

939
01:07:17,729 --> 01:07:22,647
to no longer preach that
which he could no longer
fully believe.

940
01:07:22,734 --> 01:07:34,659
And that is not hypocrisy,
that is integrity.

941
01:07:34,746 --> 01:07:37,792
And, I will not stand
with anyone

942
01:07:37,879 --> 01:07:45,670
who will denounce my friend.

943
01:07:45,757 --> 01:07:51,850
Instead, let US pray for him.

